rabbit fence
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a rabbit proof fence, with weirs and gates, that ran for extensive lengths between stations and provinces.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
